<TITLE> Bosnian parliament endorses Spiric`s return as PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sarajevo, Dec 29 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Nikola Spiric secured the approval of Bosnia's parliament to return as prime minister on Friday, promising to work on reforms that would bring Bosnia closer to membership of NATO and the European Union. Spiric resigned two months ago in protest at political changes ordered by Bosnia's international overseer aimed at ending frequent deadlocks between parties from Bosnia's two regions, the Serb Republic and the Muslim-Croat federation. The stalemates were holding up reforms, notably to Bosnia's separate police forces, being demanded by the EU before it will sign a Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) initialled on Dec. 4 -- the first rung on the ladder to eventual membership. Spiric, a Bosnian Serb, told parliament that Bosnia "does not have an alternative" to a European future. He pledged to hasten the reforms and said he hoped the SAA would be signed by the end of March. He was endorsed in parliament with 28 votes for, eight against and one abstention. Spiric resigned on Nov. 1 after international envoy Miroslav Lajcak revamped government voting rules, triggering what analysts called the worst political crisis since the end of the Bosnian war of 1992-95. The crisis was defused this month when rival ethnic leaders reached an agreement, largely in line with Lajcak's proposal, on more efficient parliamentary voting systems and on reforming their separate police forces. The EU rewarded the deal by initialling the SAA. To secure signature of the SAA, Bosnia needs to reform not only its police forces but also the public broadcasting service and the public sector. It must also improve cooperation with the U.N. war crimes tribunal in the Hague. Spiric, who is expected to reappoint his old cabinet, said the situation in Bosnia had significantly improved with regard to "dialogue and compromise". But the opposition accused him of hypocrisy, saying that the reasons he cited for his resignation had not changed
